 MECHANICS OF STOCK-TAKING IN LIBRARIES: A CASE STUDY OF INDIAN INSTITUTEOF TECHNOLOGY, DELHI.EXAMINES THE PROBLEM OF STOCK-TAKING OF BOOKS IN INDIAN LIBRARIES; DESCRIBESSTOCK-TAKING METHODS USED IN INDIA, THEIR STRONG POINTS, AND THEIRLIMITATIONS; AND DISCUSSES THE DESIRABILITY OF STOCK-TAKING. SUGGESTS THAT INLARGE LIBRARIES ONLY COMPUTER-BASED STOCK-TAKING CAN SUCCEED. DESCRIBES SUCHAN OPERATION IN THE INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY, DELHI, IN 1977 ANDPROVIDES THE COST ANALYSIS